Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Diseases of clove (_Syzygium aromaticum_, family _Myrtaceae_) due to
a number of fungi (leaf spots, blights, bud shedding, sooty mould), as
well as algal leaf spot and little leaf of suspected phytoplasma cause
have been reported.

In Indonesia, a bacterial disease of clove caused by _Ralstonia
syzygii_ was reported from Sumatra and Java, and the fungus
_Ceratocystis polychroma_ has been shown to be associated with a
serious clove decline in North Sulawesi (see links below). The report
above may refer to one or more of these pathogens.

